Move CSS-in-JS logic to `css`

Due to this change, the following now works:

```JS
styled.div({
  backgroundColor: 'blue'
})
```

Which is now aliased to

```JS
css`${{
  backgroundColor: 'blue'
}}`
```

Which works now too! So you can also do more complex, mixed things like
this:

```JS
styled.div`
border: none;
${{
  backgroundColor: 'blue'
}}
@media (max-width: 500px) {
  border: 1px solid awesome;
}
`
```

